article.description: Forwards LaToya Thomas had a season-high 23 points and Agnieszka Bibrzycka a career-high 19 in leading the Silver Stars to a 78-67 victory over the Connecticut Sun on Thursday night.
article.headline: Bibrzycka notches career-high 19
article.linkText: Thomas' season-high enough for Silver Stars
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- The San Antonio Silver Stars used big nights
from two starters to break a five-game losing streak.

Forwards LaToya Thomas had a season-high 23 points and Agnieszka
Bibrzycka a career-high 19 in leading the Silver Stars to a 78-67
victory over the Connecticut Sun on Thursday night.

Bibrzycka also contributed five rebounds and five assists.

"LaToya had a good game. Biba (Bibrzycka) played well," said
Silver Stars coach Dee Brown. "One thing I always harp on is that
your best players have to step up, everyone else follows them. It
was a solid effort for 40 minutes. Tonight was our best game of the
year."

The Silver Stars, who won only their sixth game of the year,
were paced by Adrienne Goodson with 14 points and 10 rebounds.
Margo Dydek also grabbed 10 rebounds and Shannon "Pee Wee"
Johnson had seven assists.

This was the first meeting for Johnson and her former team. She
was traded to Connecticut during the offseason for San Antonio's
first-round draft pick, which became Lindsay Whalen.

"She was wonderful," Goodson said of her teammate. "She's
having a good season considering the situation she's been put in.
It's a tough place to be."

The Silver Stars opened the second half on a 20-6 run and took a
23-point lead, 59-36, with 12:33 left in the game. Both Thomas and
Bibrzycka had six points in the run.

The Sun cut the lead to eight points with 14 seconds left on a
3-pointer by Katie Douglas. But Goodson sealed the win with two
free throws.

The Sun were led by Taj McWilliams-Franklin with 22 points,
going 9-of-10 from the field and 4-of-5 from the free throw line.

"I think they just played harder than us," said
McWilliams-Franklin. "We had a game last night and we didn't come
out strong. You don't play hard, you don't win."

Nykesha Sales also had 19 points in a game the Sun never tied or
led. Whalen had seven assists.

"They outplayed us, they outworked us, and we turned the ball
over," said Sun coach Mike Thibault. "You can't win many games
doing that."

Thomas had six of the last nine points in the first half for the
Silver Stars to send them to the locker room ahead 39-30.
